  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 3 high, 4 medium, 31 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Skopje (SKP/LWSK); plus 1 other bases. 4 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and low‑visibility procedures  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Skopje (SKP/LWSK). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Zaragoza (ZAZ/LEZG), Adolfo Suárez Madrid–Barajas (MAD/LEMD) and 9 others.",
